2429/http://www.uk.coop/organisation/1040\n|url-status=dead\n|archive-date=10 June 2015\n|title=Hawkshead & District Co-op Society Limited\n|accessdate=19 November 2013}}</ref>|| Not applicable ||1881<ref>{{cite web|url=http://mutuals.fsa.gov.uk/SocietyDetails.aspx?Number=2242&Suffix=R |title=Hawkshead and District Co-operative Society Limited, number 2242R |work=Mutuals Public Register |publisher=[[Financial Services Authority|FSA]] |accessdate=12 August 2008 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090407063252/http://mutuals.fsa.gov.uk/SocietyDetails.aspx?Number=2242&Suffix=R |archivedate=7 April 2009 }}</ref> || Unknown || Food (1)\n|-\n| [[Langdale and Neighbourhood Industrial Co-operative Society Limited|Langdale]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.uk.coop/OrganisationDisplayDetails.aspx?OrgID=39207241-38F7-416F-91DC-5D65F32EE0B3 |title=Langdale and Neighbourhood Industrial Co-operative Society Limited |work=uk.coop |publisher=Synergy arm of [[Co-operatives UK]] |accessdate=23 August 2008 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110929194105/http://www.uk.coop/OrganisationDisplayDetails.aspx?OrgID=39207241-38F7-416F-91DC-5D65F32EE0B3 |archivedate=29 September 2011 }}</ref><ref>\n{{cite web\n |url         = http://www.virsa.org/index.cfm/villageshop/Directory.Details/shop_id/176\n |title       = Langdale & Neighbourhood Industrial Co-op Society\n |work        = Shop directory\n |publisher   = [[Village Retail Services Association]]\n |accessdate  = 23 August 2008\n |url-status     = dead\n |archiveurl  = https://web.archive.org/web/20080623224934/http://www.virsa.org/index.cfm/villageshop/Directory.Details/shop_id/176\n |archivedate = 23 June 2008\n |df          = dmy-all\n}}</ref> ||langdaleco-op.co.uk<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.langdaleco-op.co.uk/ |title=Landale Co-Op |accessdate=2006-10-05 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20061005102000/http://www.langdaleco-op.co.uk/ |archivedate=5 October 2006 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> || 1884 || Unknown || Food (1)\n|-\n| [[Lincolnshire Co-operative Society|Lincolnshire]] || [http://www.lincolnshire.coop/ lincolnshire.coop] || 1861<ref>{{cite web\n |url         = http://www.lincolnshire.coop/content.asp?PageID=81&ParentCatID=&SubCatID=32\n |title       = History: 1864\n |accessdate  = 4 August 2008\n |publisher   = Lincolnshire Co-operative\n |url-status     = dead\n |archiveurl  = https://web.archive.org/web/20110718162705/http://www.lincolnshire.coop/content.asp?PageID=81&ParentCatID=&SubCatID=32\n |archivedate = 18 July 2011\n |df          = dmy-all\n}}</ref> || 228,000 || Food (84), Bakery (1), Petrol Stations (10), Pharmacies (48), Post Offices (40), Travel (13), Funeral (17), Coffee Shops (2).\n|-\n| [[Midcounties Co-operative Society|Midcounties]]  || [http://www.midcounties.coop/ midcounties.coop] || 1853 ||  667,000<ref>{{cite report|title=2017/18 Annual Report and Accounts|publisher=The Midcounties Co-operative|url=https://www.midcounties.coop/siteassets/reports/2017-2018-annual-report--accounts.pdf}}</ref>  || [[Midcounties Co-operative#Energy|Energy]], Food (244), Funeral (78), Travel (58), Pharmacies (46),  Childcare (47), Post Offices (74), Co-operative Flexible Benefits<ref>{{cite report|url=http://www.midcounties.coop/PageFiles/2364/AGM1415.pdf|format=PDF|title=Annual Report & Accounts 2014/15|publisher=    The Midcounties Cooperative|date=2015|accessdate=15 February 2016}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Radstock Co-operative Society|Radstock]] || [http://www.radstockcoop.co.uk/ radstockcoop.co.uk]|| 1867 || Unknown || Food (14), Non-food (1)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.radstockcoop.co.uk/store|title=Stores|publisher=Radstock Co-op|accessdate=20 February 2014}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Scottish Midland Co-op|Scotmid]] || [http://www.scotmid.coop/ scotmid.coop] || 1859 ||  268,125<ref>{{cite report|title=Annual Report & Financial Accounts for year ended 27 January 2018|publisher=Scottish Midland Co-operative Society Ltd|url=https://www.scotmid.coop/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/Scotmid_AnnualReport_Full_2018.pdf}}</ref>|| Food (129)\n|-\n| [[Southern Co-operatives|Southern]] || [https://www.thesouthernco-operative.co.uk/ thesouthernco-operative.co.uk] || 1873 ||  157,000<ref>{{cite report|title=Southern Co-op Annual Review 2017\u201318|url=http://www.thesouthernco-operative.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/COOP6559_AR_2017_FULL-Single-144_AW_010518.pdf|publisher=Southern Co-op}}</ref>|| Food (197), Funeral (16)\n|-\n| [[Tamworth Co-operative Society|Tamworth]] || [http://www.tamworth.coop/ tamworth.coop] || 1886 || Unknown || Food (14), Non-Food (1), Funeral (7)\n|-\n|}\n\n==Awards==\n[[File:Elizabeth II at an office opening.jpg|thumb|[[Queen Elizabeth II]] at the opening of an office declared the \"most environmentally-friendly building in the world\", November 2013]]\nIn 2002 the society gained [[Worldaware]]'s 2002 ''Shell Award for [[Sustainable Development]]'' for its use of [[Fairtrade]] goods.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.worldaware.org.uk/awards/awards2002/coop.html|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20030719015604/http://www.worldaware.org.uk/awards/awards2002/coop.html|url-status=dead|archive-date=19 July 2003|title=2002 Shell Worldaware Business Award|publisher=Worldaware|accessdate=18 February 2007}}</ref> and in 2007 it won a [[Queen's Award for Enterprise]] in the Sustainable Development category, in recognition of its business practices, including its pioneering stance on Fairtrade and the environment.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.queensawards.org.uk/business/Winners/2007.html#sustainabledevelopment|title=Winners 2007|accessdate=13 May 2008|publisher=[[Queen's Awards for Enterprise]]|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100329182415/http://www.queensawards.org.uk/business/Winners/2007.html#sustainabledevelopment|archivedate=29 March 2010|df=dmy-all}}</ref> In January 2010, the society appeared on the shortlist for the Transform Awards for rebranding and brand transformation in a number of categories<ref>{{cite web|title=Shortlist announced for the Transform Awards for rebranding|url=http://www.communicatemagazine.co.uk/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=886:shortlist-announced-for-the-transform-awards-for-rebranding&catid=1:stories&Itemid=115|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111008052049/http://www.communicatemagazine.co.uk/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=886%3Ashortlist-announced-for-the-transform-awards-for-rebranding&catid=1%3Astories&Itemid=115|url-status=dead|archive-date=8 October 2011|publisher=Communicate magazine|date=January 2010|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\nA 2011 ''[[Which?]]'' survey claimed that the Co-operative was the least favourite grocer with 46% satisfaction among customers compared to [[Waitrose]] which achieved 85%.<ref>{{cite news|title=Waitrose tops supermarket survey|url=http://www.which.co.uk/news/2011/01/waitrose-tops-supermarket-survey-242420|work=Which? News|author=Alice Rickman|date=26 Jan 2011}}</ref>\n\nThe Co-operative Bank has consistently been one of the highest-rated banks in the UK for customer satisfaction.<ref>{{cite web|title=Best and worst banks|url=http://www.which.co.uk/money/bank-accounts/reviews-ns/bank-accounts/best-banks-for-customer-satisfaction/|website=Which?|author=Chiara Cavaglieri|date=September 2018}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[British co-operative movement]]\n* [[The Co-operative brand]]\n\n==Notes==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==References==\n* [[Louis Brandeis]], ''[[Other People's Money And How the Bankers Use It]]'' (1914) ch 10\n* Percy Redfern,''The Story of the CWS 1863\u20131913 (1913)''\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category}}\n* {{official website}}\n* [http://www.thekellyreview.co.uk The Kelly Review]\n\n{{Co-operative Group|state=expanded}}\n{{UK consumer co-ops}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Co-Operative Group}}\n[[Category:Business services companies established in 1844]]\n[[Category:Consumers' co-operatives of the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:Companies based in Manchester]]\n[[Category:Funeral directors in the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:Defunct department stores of the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:1844 establishments in the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:The Co-operative Group| ]]\n", "name_user": "Polly Tunnel", "label": "safe", "comment": "ref filling\u2192\u200eClean energy campaigning", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Co-operative_Group"}
{"title_page": "Quintessentially Group", "text_new": "{{short description|British concierge company founded in 2000}}\n{{EngvarB|date=October 2017}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2017}}\n{{Infobox company\n| name = Quintessentially Group\n| logo =\n| logo_size = 200px\n| former_name = \n| type = Privately held company\n| industry = [[Lifestyle management]]\n| founded = 2000\n| founders = [[Aaron Simpson (entrepreneur)|Aaron Simpson]]<br />[[Ben Elliot]]<br />Paul Drummond\n| hq_location = London, England\n| hq_location_country = United Kingdom\n| num_locations = 60\n| key_people = [[Annastasia Seebohm]], Global CEO<br/>\n| products = \n| brands = \n| services = Concierge and Lifestyle Management services<ref>{{cite web| url=https://www.forbes.com/2003/02/26/cx_as_0226feat.html| title=Beyond The Black Card?| author=Afsun Smith| date=26 February 2003| work=Forbes| accessdate=6 February 2015}}</ref>\n| revenue = US$ 100,000,000 (2017)\n| members_year = \n| num_employees = 1,000\n| num_employees_year = 2019<ref>{{cite web| url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/finance/newsbysector/banksandfinance/privateequity/11232532/Quintessentially-hopes-its-fixers-can-fetch-120m.html| title=Quintessentially hopes its fixers can fetch \u00a3120m| author=Ashley Armstrong| date=15 November 2014| work=The Daily Telegraph| accessdate=6 February 2015}}</ref>\n| divisions = \n| subsid = \n| homepage = {{url|quintessentially.com}}\n}}\n\n'''Quintessentially Group''' is a British concierge company founded in 2000 by [[Aaron Simpson (entrepreneur)|Aaron Simpson]], [[Ben Elliot]] and [[Paul Drummond]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/media/2007/jul/29/pressandpublishing.business2 |title=Guardian Media Group: Luxury magazines have designs on readers with the deepest pockets of all |work=The Guardian |accessdate=19 January 2011 |location=London |first=James |last=Robinson |date=30 July 2007}}</ref> The company is headquartered in London<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www1.investhk.gov.hk/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/2011.09-quintessentially-en.pdf |title=Quintessentially Sees Hong Kong as a Natural Fit for its HQ}}</ref> and operates 60 offices worldwide.<ref name=nyt14>{{cite web| url=https://www.nytimes.com/2014/12/18/style/a-gift-so-right-shell-know-you-got-help.html| title=A Gift So Right, She'll Know You Got Help| author=Marrhew Schneier| date=17 December 2014| work=The New York Times| accessdate=6 February 2015}}</ref> Quintessentially is a members-only \"[[:wikt:luxury|luxury]] [[lifestyle management]] service\" that provides concierge services including travel bookings, restaurant recommendations, and access to events.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2005/12/08/realestate/08iht-regift6.html|title=When it's the gardener's day offand the topiary really needs a trim|date=8 December 2005|work=The New York Times|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5x3bxxBNy|archivedate=9 March 2011}}</ref> Quintessentially Group includes 16 brand services, including Travel, Events, Estates and the Quintessentially Foundation.<ref name=lux>{{cite web| url=http://www.luxworldwide.com/magazine/lifestyle/quintessentially-the-luxury-lifestyle/| title=Quintessentially: The Luxury Lifestyle| date=21 July 2012| publisher=Lux Worldwide| accessdate=6 February 2015}}</ref><ref name=bizbash>{{cite web| url=http://www.bizbash.com/quintessentially_opens_event_division_in_new_york_hires_new_director/new-york/story/13126/| title=Quintessentially Opens Event Division in New York, Hires New Director| author=Lauren Matison| date=23 October 2008| publisher=BizBash| accessdate=6 February 2015}}</ref><ref name=bizin>{{cite web| url=http://www.businessinsider.com/quintessentially-private-concierge-service-2012-3| title=A Personal Concierge Service That Will Do Your Errands\u2014And Book You A Yacht on the French Riviera| author=Matthew Kassel| date=8 March 2012| publisher=Business Insider| accessdate=6 February 2015}}</ref> [[Annastasia Seebohm]] is the company's global chief executive officer.<ref>https://www.forbes.com/sites/carriehammer/2018/04/04/meet-the-queen-of-luxury/#635bf28cbd05</ref>\n\n==History==\nQuintessentially was established in 2000 by [[Aaron Simpson (entrepreneur)|Aaron Simpson]], Paul Drummond and [[Ben Elliot]], the nephew of the [[Camilla, Duchess of Cornwall]].<ref name=money>{{cite web| url=http://www.thisismoney.co.uk/money/markets/article-2545889/Pandering-jet-set-sends-profits-soaring-concierge-group-Quintessentially.html| title=Pandering to the jet set sends profits soaring at concierge group Quintessentially| author=Sarah Bridge| date=25 January 2014| publisher=This is Money| accessdate=6 February 2015}}</ref><ref name=nine>{{cite web|last1=Jacobs|first1=Emma|title=21st Century Butlers|url=http://www.ft.com/cms/s/2/90ba14cc-0709-11e0-94f1-00144feabdc0.html|work=Financial Times|accessdate=20 December 2010}}</ref> Simpson met Drummond at [[Oxford University]] and later started the company with business partner Elliot as a small, London-based concierge service.<ref name=tele11>{{cite web| url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/celebritynews/my-perfect-weekend/8838178/My-perfect-weekend-Ben-Elliot.html| title=My perfect weekend: Ben Elliot| author=Anna Tyzack| date=20 October 2011| work=The Daily Telegraph| accessdate=6 February 2015}}</ref> Before founding Quintessentially, Elliot had co-founded K-Bar Plc, a group of nightclubs and bars, and Simpson had worked as a film producer.<ref name=traveler>{{cite web| url=http://www.elitetraveler.com/leaders-in-luxury/ben-elliot| title=Leaders in Luxury Ben Elliot| date=5 February 2009| publisher=Elite Traveler| accessdate=6 February 2015}}</ref>\n\nFrom 2002 to 2005, Quintessentially expanded from two offices in the United Kingdom to ten around the world.<ref name=\"ten\"/> In 2018 the company reports to over 60+ offices in cities such as Dubai, Hong Kong, London, Los Angeles and New York.\n\nIn 2010, the company was estimated to have about 86,000 subscribers, including 800 billionaires.<ref name=\"reuters\">{{cite web|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/2010/06/03/us-luxury-summit-quintessentially-idUSTRE6522YN20100603|title=Quintessentially goes upmarket to beat recession|author=Mark Potter|date=3 June 2010|accessdate=6 February 2015|agency=Reuters}}</ref> Quintessentially moved its headquarters from [[Soho]] to [[Portland Place]] in early 2011.<ref name=ft2011>{{cite web| url=http://www.ft.com/intl/cms/s/0/37669c60-cff9-11e0-81e2-00144feabdc0.html| title=Business Diary: Ben Elliot, Quintessentially| date=29 August 2011| work=Financial Times| accessdate=6 February 2015}}</ref> The company grew over 20 percent during 2012 from \u00a313.5million in turnover to \u00a316.7million by April 2013.<ref name=money/> In 2017, the group's total turnover was $100 million.<ref name=tim/>\n\nThe Quintessentially Lifestyle App was introduced in early 2014. The [[mobile app]] features recommendations, reviews, and allows members to make requests to their Lifestyle Managers.<ref>{{cite web|last1=King|first1=Jen|title=Quintessentially Lifestyle app uses geolocation to curate concierge experience|url=http://www.luxurydaily.com/quintessentially-lifestyle-app-uses-geolocation-to-curate-concierge-experience/|work=Luxury Daily|accessdate=19 March 2014}}</ref> In November 2016, Quintessentially partnered with [[Eva Longoria]] and [[Victoria Beckham]] to host the seventh annual Global Gift Gala at the [[Corinthia Hotel]] in London.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://us.hellomagazine.com/celebrities/2016102734299/victoria-beckham-and-eva-longoria-unite-for-global-gift-gala/|title=Best Friends Victoria Beckham and Eva Longoria Unite for a Good Cause|work=Hello|date=27 October 2016|access-date=12 December 2016}}</ref> In 2017, it was announced that the company was building a \"super yacht\" for its members.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://edition.pagesuite-professional.co.uk/html5/reader/production/default.aspx?pubname=&edid=42fb4a8f-6485-4055-97f7-c74e5e4927e7%7Ctitle=At|title=PageSuite|access-date=30 May 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/business-39691931|title=Mr Fixer: The man who can arrange anything for you|last=Smale|first=Will|date=1 May 2017|publisher=BBC News|access-date=30 May 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Operations==\nQuintessentially Group is a network of 16 brand services that operate the personal services provided for its private members.<ref name=bizin/> These companies include Travel, Events and Estates,<ref name=ftest>{{cite web| url=http://www.ft.com/intl/cms/s/2f326b64-66a1-11de-a034-00144feabdc0,Authorised=false.html?_i_location=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.ft.com%2Fcms%2Fs%2F0%2F2f326b64-66a1-11de-a034-00144feabdc0.html%3Fsiteedition%3Dintl&siteedition=intl&_i_referer=| title=The TV or Radio Is Always On| author=Angus Watson| date=4 July 2009| work=Financial Times| accessdate=6 February 2015}}</ref> and Quintessentially Gifts.<ref name=nyt14/>\n\n===Quintessentially Lifestyle===\nQuintessentially Lifestyle is a members-only luxury lifestyle management and concierge service.<ref name=nine/> ''[[The New York Times]]'' called Quintessentially Lifestyle, \"The company that transformed the idea of concierge services into 'lifestyle management.'\"<ref name=ten>{{cite web|last1=Pham|first1=Lisa|title=Hey, Big Spender, You Want Value?|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2009/10/24/business/global/24concierge.html?pagewanted=all&_r=2&|work=The New York Times|accessdate=23 October 2009}}</ref> It provides Corporate Solutions{{solution-inline|date=August 2019}} and Private Memberships that include preferential rates on hotels and other reservations, access to events, luxury gifts, and other services.<ref name=bizin/><ref name=\"elite\">{{cite web|url=http://www.elitetraveler.com/travel/travel-news/membership-to-quintessentially-the-ultimate-christmas-gift|title=Membership To Quintessentially \u2013 The Ultimate Christmas Gift|date=17 October 2008|publisher=Elite Traveler|accessdate=6 February 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Yan|first1=Cathy|title=What's Hot on the Concierge List|url=https://blogs.wsj.com/hong-kong/2010/11/24/whats-hot-on-the-concierge-list/|work=The Wall Street Journal|accessdate=24 November 2010}}</ref> \n\nGlobally, the firm employs more than 1500 Lifestyle Managers in over 60 offices speaking 35 languages.<ref>{{cite web|title=Quintessentially's Most Extravagant Requests |url=http://www.esquire.co.uk/culture/article/4698/quintessentiallys-most-extravagant-requests/ |publisher=Esquire |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130901174330/http://www.esquire.co.uk/culture/article/4698/quintessentiallys-most-extravagant-requests/ |archivedate=2013-09-01 |accessdate=22 October 2017}}{{better source|date=October 2017|reason=no mention of the number of managers in the archived source}}</ref>\n\n===Quintessentially Foundation===\nEstablished in June 2008, the Quintessentially Foundation is the charitable arm of the Group.<ref name=ft2011/> It has raised more than \u00a39,000,000 through various [[fundraisers]], including the annual Poker Night.<ref name=chartwell>{{cite web| url=http://chartwell-media.com/journal/the-quintessentially-foundation-gives-guests-the-chance-to-play-their-hand-for-a-great-cause/| title=The Quintessentially Foundation Gives Guests The Chance to Play to Their Hand For a Great Cause| accessdate=6 February 2015}}</ref> In 2013, the annual Poker Night fundraiser generated \u00a3160,000 for the Duchenne Children's Trust that funds research for the development of a cure for [[Duchenne muscular dystrophy]].<ref name=mail>{{cite web| url=http://diary.mailonsunday.co.uk/2013/10/quintessentially-foundation-annual-poker-night-at-the-savoy-hotel.html| title=Quintessentially Foundation Annual Poker Night at the Savoy Hotel| author=Juliet Conway| date=11 October 2013| work=Daily Mail| accessdate=6 February 2015}}</ref> The foundation has supported organisations like [[Room to Read]] and has also funded medical research to find a cure for [[Type 1 diabetes]].<ref name=traveler/> The company has also organised a 500 kilometre rickshaw race in [[India]] to raise money for elephant protection.<ref name =tim>{{cite web|url=http://www.thisismoney.co.uk/money/news/article-3223583/We-tracking-customers-s-valuable-information-Meet-upmarket-fixer-knows-habits-super-rich.html|title=Need That Table, Ticket, or Rare Item? Meet Aaron Simpson the Upmarket Fixer Who Knows the Habits of the Super Rich|publisher=This is Money |first=Sarah |last=Bridge |date=5 September 2015|access-date=30 October 2015}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|33em}}\n\n[[Category:British brands]]\n[[Category:Conglomerate companies of the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:Luxury brands]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|British concierge company founded in 2000}}\n{{EngvarB|date=October 2017}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2017}}\n{{Infobox company\n| name = Quintessentially Group\n| logo =\n| logo_size = 200px\n| former_name = \n| type = Privately held company\n| industry = [[Lifestyle management]]\n| founded = 2000\n| founders = [[Aaron Simpson (entrepreneur)|Aaron Simpson]]<br />[[Ben Elliot]]<br />Paul Drummond\n| hq_location = London, England\n| hq_location_country = United Kingdom\n| num_locations = 60\n| key_people = [[Annastasia Seebohm]], Global CEO<br/>\n| products = \n| brands = \n| services = Concierge and Lifestyle Management services<ref>{{cite web| url=https://www.forbes.com/2003/02/26/cx_as_0226feat.html| title=Beyond The Black Card?| author=Afsun Smith| date=26 February 2003| work=Forbes| accessdate=6 February 2015}}</ref>\n| revenue = US$ 100,000,000 (2017)\n| members_year = \n| num_employees = 1,000\n| num_employees_year = 2019<ref>{{cite web| url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/finance/newsbysector/banksandfinance/privateequity/11232532/Quintessentially-hopes-its-fixers-can-fetch-120m.html| title=Quintessentially hopes its fixers can fetch \u00a3120m| author=Ashley Armstrong| date=15 November 2014| work=The Daily Telegraph| accessdate=6 February 2015}}</ref>\n| divisions = \n| subsid = \n| homepage = {{url|quintessentially.com}}\n}}\n\n'''Quintessentially Group''' is a British concierge company founded in 2000 by [[Aaron Simpson (entrepreneur)|Aaron Simpson]], [[Ben Elliot]] and [[Paul Drummond]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/media/2007/jul/29/pressandpublishing.business2 |title=Guardian Media Group: Luxury magazines have designs on readers with the deepest pockets of all |work=The Guardian |accessdate=19 January 2011 |location=London |first=James |last=Robinson |date=30 July 2007}}</ref> The company is headquartered in London<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www1.investhk.gov.hk/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/2011.09-quintessentially-en.pdf |title=Quintessentially Sees Hong Kong as a Natural Fit for its HQ}}</ref> and operates 60 offices worldwide.<ref name=nyt14>{{cite web| url=https://www.nytimes.com/2014/12/18/style/a-gift-so-right-shell-know-you-got-help.html| title=A Gift So Right, She'll Know You Got Help| author=Marrhew Schneier| date=17 December 2014| work=The New York Times| accessdate=6 February 2015}}</ref> Quintessentially is a members-only \"[[:wikt:luxury|luxury]] [[lifestyle management]] service\" that provides concierge services including travel bookings, restaurant recommendations, and access to events.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2005/12/08/realestate/08iht-regift6.html|title=When it's the gardener's day offand the topiary really needs a trim|date=8 December 2005|work=The New York Times|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5x3bxxBNy|archivedate=9 March 2011}}</ref> Quintessentially Group includes 16 brand services, including Travel, Events, Estates and the Quintessentially Foundation.<ref name=lux>{{cite web| url=http://www.luxworldwide.com/magazine/lifestyle/quintessentially-the-luxury-lifestyle/| title=Quintessentially: The Luxury Lifestyle| date=21 July 2012| publisher=Lux Worldwide| accessdate=6 February 2015}}</ref><ref name=bizbash>{{cite web| url=http://www.bizbash.com/quintessentially_opens_event_division_in_new_york_hires_new_director/new-york/story/13126/| title=Quintessentially Opens Event Division in New York, Hires New Director| author=Lauren Matison| date=23 October 2008| publisher=BizBash| accessdate=6 February 2015}}</ref><ref name=bizin>{{cite web| url=http://www.businessinsider.com/quintessentially-private-concierge-service-2012-3| title=A Personal Concierge Service That Will Do Your Errands\u2014And Book You A Yacht on the French Riviera| author=Matthew Kassel| date=8 March 2012| publisher=Business Insider| accessdate=6 February 2015}}</ref> [[Annastasia Seebohm]] is the company's global chief executive officer.<ref>https://www.forbes.com/sites/carriehammer/2018/04/04/meet-the-queen-of-luxury/#635bf28cbd05</ref>\n\n==History==\nQuintessentially was established in 2000 by [[Aaron Simpson (entrepreneur)|Aaron Simpson]], Paul Drummond and [[Ben Elliot]], the nephew of the [[Camilla, Duchess of Cornwall]].<ref name=money>{{cite web| url=http://www.thisismoney.co.uk/money/markets/article-2545889/Pandering-jet-set-sends-profits-soaring-concierge-group-Quintessentially.html| title=Pandering to the jet set sends profits soaring at concierge group Quintessentially| author=Sarah Bridge| date=25 January 2014| publisher=This is Money| accessdate=6 February 2015}}</ref><ref name=nine>{{cite web|last1=Jacobs|first1=Emma|title=21st Century Butlers|url=http://www.ft.com/cms/s/2/90ba14cc-0709-11e0-94f1-00144feabdc0.html|work=Financial Times|accessdate=20 December 2010}}</ref> Simpson met Drummond at [[Oxford University]] and later started the company with business partner Elliot as a small, London-based concierge service.<ref name=tele11>{{cite web| url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/celebritynews/my-perfect-weekend/8838178/My-perfect-weekend-Ben-Elliot.html| title=My perfect weekend: Ben Elliot| author=Anna Tyzack| date=20 October 2011| work=The Daily Telegraph| accessdate=6 February 2015}}</ref> Before founding Quintessentially, Elliot had co-founded K-Bar Plc, a group of nightclubs and bars, and Simpson had worked as a film producer.<ref name=traveler>{{cite web| url=http://www.elitetraveler.com/leaders-in-luxury/ben-elliot| title=Leaders in Luxury Ben Elliot| date=5 February 2009| publisher=Elite Traveler| accessdate=6 February 2015}}</ref>\n\nFrom 2002 to 2005, Quintessentially expanded from two offices in the United Kingdom to ten around the world.<ref name=\"ten\"/> In 2018 the company reports to over 60+ offices in cities such as Dubai, Hong Kong, London, Los Angeles and New York.\n\nIn 2010, the company was estimated to have about 86,000 subscribers, including 800 billionaires.<ref name=\"reuters\">{{cite web|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/2010/06/03/us-luxury-summit-quintessentially-idUSTRE6522YN20100603|title=Quintessentially goes upmarket to beat recession|author=Mark Potter|date=3 June 2010|accessdate=6 February 2015|agency=Reuters}}</ref> Quintessentially moved its headquarters from [[Soho]] to [[Portland Place]] in early 2011.<ref name=ft2011>{{cite web| url=http://www.ft.com/intl/cms/s/0/37669c60-cff9-11e0-81e2-00144feabdc0.html| title=Business Diary: Ben Elliot, Quintessentially| date=29 August 2011| work=Financial Times| accessdate=6 February 2015}}</ref> The company grew over 20 percent during 2012 from \u00a313.5million in turnover to \u00a316.7million by April 2013.<ref name=money/> In 2017, the group's total turnover was $100 million.<ref name=tim/>\n\nThe Quintessentially Lifestyle App was introduced in early 2014. The [[mobile app]] features recommendations, reviews, and allows members to make requests to their Lifestyle Managers.<ref>{{cite web|last1=King|first1=Jen|title=Quintessentially Lifestyle app uses geolocation to curate concierge experience|url=http://www.luxurydaily.com/quintessentially-lifestyle-app-uses-geolocation-to-curate-concierge-experience/|work=Luxury Daily|accessdate=19 March 2014}}</ref> In November 2016, Quintessentially partnered with [[Eva Longoria]] and [[Victoria Beckham]] to host the seventh annual Global Gift Gala at the [[Corinthia Hotel]] in London.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://us.hellomagazine.com/celebrities/2016102734299/victoria-beckham-and-eva-longoria-unite-for-global-gift-gala/|title=Best Friends Victoria Beckham and Eva Longoria Unite for a Good Cause|work=Hello|date=27 October 2016|access-date=12 December 2016}}</ref> In 2017, it was announced that the company was building a \"super yacht\" for its members.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://edition.pagesuite-professional.co.uk/html5/reader/production/default.aspx?pubname=&edid=42fb4a8f-6485-4055-97f7-c74e5e4927e7%7Ctitle=At|title=PageSuite|access-date=30 May 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/business-39691931|title=Mr Fixer: The man who can arrange anything for you|last=Smale|first=Will|date=1 May 2017|publisher=BBC News|access-date=30 May 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Operations==\nQuintessentially Group is a network of 16 brand services that operate the personal services provided for its private members.<ref name=bizin/> These companies include Travel, Events and Estates,<ref name=ftest>{{cite web| url=http://www.ft.com/intl/cms/s/2f326b64-66a1-11de-a034-00144feabdc0,Authorised=false.html?_i_location=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.ft.com%2Fcms%2Fs%2F0%2F2f326b64-66a1-11de-a034-00144feabdc0.html%3Fsiteedition%3Dintl&siteedition=intl&_i_referer=| title=The TV or Radio Is Always On| author=Angus Watson| date=4 July 2009| work=Financial Times| accessdate=6 February 2015}}</ref> and Quintessentially Gifts.<ref name=nyt14/>\n\n===Quintessentially Lifestyle===\nQuintessentially Lifestyle is a members-only luxury lifestyle management and concierge service.<ref name=nine/> ''[[The New York Times]]'' called Quintessentially Lifestyle, \"The company that transformed the idea of concierge services into 'lifestyle management.'\"<ref name=ten>{{cite web|last1=Pham|first1=Lisa|title=Hey, Big Spender, You Want Value?|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2009/10/24/business/global/24concierge.html?pagewanted=all&_r=2&|work=The New York Times|accessdate=23 October 2009}}</ref> It provides Corporate Solutions{{solution-inline|date=August 2019}} and Private Memberships that include preferential rates on hotels and other reservations, access to events, luxury gifts, and other services.<ref name=bizin/><ref name=\"elite\">{{cite web|url=http://www.elitetraveler.com/travel/travel-news/membership-to-quintessentially-the-ultimate-christmas-gift|title=Membership To Quintessentially \u2013 The Ultimate Christmas Gift|date=17 October 2008|publisher=Elite Traveler|accessdate=6 February 2015}}</ref>\n\n<ref>{{cite web|last1=Yan|first1=Cathy|title=What's Hot on the Concierge List|url=https://blogs.wsj.com/hong-kong/2010/11/24/whats-hot-on-the-concierge-list/|work=The Wall Street Journal|accessdate=24 November 2010}}</ref> Globally, the firm employs more than 1500 Lifestyle Managers in over 60 offices speaking 35 languages.<ref>{{cite web|title=Quintessentially's Most Extravagant Requests |url=http://www.esquire.co.uk/culture/article/4698/quintessentiallys-most-extravagant-requests/ |publisher=Esquire |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130901174330/http://www.esquire.co.uk/culture/article/4698/quintessentiallys-most-extravagant-requests/ |archivedate=2013-09-01 |accessdate=22 October 2017}}{{better source|date=October 2017|reason=no mention of the number of managers in the archived source}}</ref>\n\n===Quintessentially Foundation===\nEstablished in June 2008, the Quintessentially Foundation is the charitable arm of the Group.<ref name=ft2011/> It has raised more than \u00a39,000,000 through various [[fundraisers]], including the annual Poker Night.<ref name=chartwell>{{cite web| url=http://chartwell-media.com/journal/the-quintessentially-foundation-gives-guests-the-chance-to-play-their-hand-for-a-great-cause/| title=The Quintessentially Foundation Gives Guests The Chance to Play to Their Hand For a Great Cause| accessdate=6 February 2015}}</ref> In 2013, the annual Poker Night fundraiser generated \u00a3160,000 for the Duchenne Children's Trust that funds research for the development of a cure for [[Duchenne muscular dystrophy]].<ref name=mail>{{cite web| url=http://diary.mailonsunday.co.uk/2013/10/quintessentially-foundation-annual-poker-night-at-the-savoy-hotel.html| title=Quintessentially Foundation Annual Poker Night at the Savoy Hotel| author=Juliet Conway| date=11 October 2013| work=Daily Mail| accessdate=6 February 2015}}</ref> The foundation has supported organisations like [[Room to Read]] and has also funded medical research to find a cure for [[Type 1 diabetes]].<ref name=traveler/> The company has also organised a 500 kilometre rickshaw race in [[India]] to raise money for elephant protection.<ref name =tim>{{cite web|url=http://www.thisismoney.co.uk/money/news/article-3223583/We-tracking-customers-s-valuable-information-Meet-upmarket-fixer-knows-habits-super-rich.html|title=Need That Table, Ticket, or Rare Item? Meet Aaron Simpson the Upmarket Fixer Who Knows the Habits of the Super Rich|publisher=This is Money |first=Sarah |last=Bridge |date=5 September 2015|access-date=30 October 2015}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|33em}}\n\n[[Category:British brands]]\n[[Category:Conglomerate companies of the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:Luxury brands]]\n", "name_user": "The Eloquent Peasant", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eQuintessentially Lifestyle:format", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Quintessentially_Group"}
{"title_page": "Hyde Park Schools", "text_new": "{{Unreferenced|date=August 2019}}\n{{Infobox school\n| name    = Hyde Park Schools\n| motto   = We believe that HPBS exists to glorify God through the ministry of an excellent Christ-centered education.\n| address = 11400 North Mo-Pac Expressway\n| city    = [[Austin, Texas|Austin]]\n| state   = [[Texas]]\n| zipcode = 78759\n| country = [[United States]]\n| coordinates = {{coord|30.408215|-97.731984|type:edu|display=inline,title}}\n| type    = Private\n| established = 1968 (Primary School) / 1980 (High School)\n| authorizer  = Emery\n| campus  = Two\n| students = 300\n| homepage = http://www.hpbs.org/\n}}\n\n'''Hyde Park Schools''' is a [[private school|private]] [[Christian school|Christian]] K-12 located in [[Austin, Texas]]. Hyde Park has two campuses: the Speedway Campus for 4K through 8th grades campus and the Quarries Campus for high school.<ref>[https://www.hp-schools.org/ Home]. Hyde Park Schools. Retrieved on May 21, 2019. \"Speedway Campus 4K-8th Grade 3901 Speedway  Austin Texas 78751 [...] Quarries Campus High School 11400 N. Mopac Expwy. Austin Texas 78759\"</ref>\n\n== History ==\n\nHyde Park High School was founded in 1980, and is associated with the [[Baptist]] denomination of [[Christianity]].{{Citation needed|date=September 2009|reason=many flavors of Baptist}} Hyde Park has a [[University-preparatory school|college-preparatory]] program that emphasizes Christian values.\n\n== Campuses ==\n{{OSM Location map\n|float = left\n|width=275\n| coord = {{coord|30.352164|-97.731805}}              \n| mark-coord  = {{coord|30.302164 |-97.731805 }} |label =Speedway (PK-8)<!--3901 Speedway  Austin Texas 78751-->   |label-pos  = left\n| mark-coord2 = {{coord|30.408317  |-97.731756 }} |label2=Quarries (9-12)<!-- -->  |label-pos2 = right\n| zoom = 11              <!--(1=whole world, 18=a street)-->\n| caption = Campuses in Austin\n}}\n\nHyde Park High School is a ministry of Hyde Park Baptist Church in Austin, Texas. The High School is located at 11400 N. Mopac, Austin, Texas. Enrollment generally runs from 200-300 students. It moved to this location in the fall of 2009. Before this time it was located at 3901 Speedway with the Elementary and Middle School campuses. It was founded in 1980 by Bob Edd Shotwell, who also founded Hyde Park Baptist Elementary in 1968.\n\n== Associations ==\n\nThe school is now a member of the [[Association of Christian Schools International]] (ACSI), the [[Southern Baptist]] Association of Christian Schools (SBACS), and Texas Association of Private and Parochial Schools (TAPPS).{{Citation needed|date=September 2009|reason=Those should probably be sourced or dropped.}}\n\n== Extracurricular activities ==\n===Sports===\nHyde Park athletics is led by [[athletic director]]/head [[American football|football]] coach Dean Campbell. Dean Campbell has coached at the college football level at many different universities, including the University of Texas, Texas A&M University, Texas Tech, Arkansas, and Air Force. Campbell's goal for Hyde Park athletics is stated as \"One foundational goal for our program is to provide strong leadership for our student athletes through the Christian role models of our coaches.\"\n* [[American football|Football]]\n* [[Volleyball]]\n* [[Basketball]] (Boys and Girls)\n* [[Cross Country Running|Cross Country]]\n* [[Track and field|Track]]\n* [[Association football|Soccer]] (Boys and Girls)\n* [[Golf]]\n* [[Baseball]]\n* [[Softball]]\n* [[Tennis]] (Boys and Girls)\n* [[Cheerleading]]\n* [[Ultimate Frisbee]]\n* [[Flag Football]]\n* [[ indoor birdwatching]]\n\n===Fine arts===\n* Prancers ([[Drill team#Texas|Drill team]])\n* Joyful Noise ([[honors student|Honors]] [[choir]])\n* Robotics [[Kelly Flores]]\nWe also have underwater pottery and indoor birdwatching a sour fine arts. Our school can be used as a prison and we have a gourmet lunch service called haute launch. I found a hair in my food once :)\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.hpbs.org/pages/page.asp?page_id=37524 Official site]\n* [http://www.hpbs.org/pages/page.asp?page_id=39733 ACLA home page]\n{{Travis County, Texas Schools}}\n{{TAPPS 5A}}\n\n[[Category:Baptist schools in the United States]]\n[[Category:Christian schools in Texas]]\n[[Category:Educational institutions established in 1968]]\n[[Category:High schools in Austin, Texas]]\n[[Category:Private high schools in Texas]]\n\n\n{{Texas-high-school-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Unreferenced|date=August 2019}}\n{{Infobox school\n| name    = Hyde Park Schools\n| motto   = We believe that HPBS exists to glorify God through the ministry of an excellent Christ-centered education.\n| address = 11400 North Mo-Pac Expressway\n| city    = [[Austin, Texas|Austin]]\n| state   = [[Texas]]\n| zipcode = 78759\n| country = [[United States]]\n| coordinates = {{coord|30.408215|-97.731984|type:edu|display=inline,title}}\n| type    = Private\n| established = 1968 (Primary School) / 1980 (High School)\n| authorizer  = Emery\n| campus  = Two\n| students = 300\n| homepage = http://www.hpbs.org/\n}}\n\n'''Hyde Park Schools''' is a [[private school|private]] [[Christian school|Christian]] K-12 located in [[Austin, Texas]]. Hyde Park has two campuses: the Speedway Campus for 4K through 8th grades campus and the Quarries Campus for high school.<ref>[https://www.hp-schools.org/ Home]. Hyde Park Schools. Retrieved on May 21, 2019. \"Speedway Campus 4K-8th Grade 3901 Speedway  Austin Texas 78751 [...] Quarries Campus High School 11400 N. Mopac Expwy. Austin Texas 78759\"</ref>\n\n== History ==\n\nHyde Park High School was founded in 1980, and is associated with the [[Baptist]] denomination of [[Christianity]].{{Citation needed|date=September 2009|reason=many flavors of Baptist}} Hyde Park has a [[University-preparatory school|college-preparatory]] program that emphasizes Christian values.\n\n== Campuses ==\n{{OSM Location map\n|float = left\n|width=275\n| coord = {{coord|30.352164|-97.731805}}              \n| mark-coord  = {{coord|30.302164 |-97.731805 }} |label =Speedway (PK-8)<!--3901 Speedway  Austin Texas 78751-->   |label-pos  = left\n| mark-coord2 = {{coord|30.408317  |-97.731756 }} |label2=Quarries (9-12)<!-- -->  |label-pos2 = right\n| zoom = 11              <!--(1=whole world, 18=a street)-->\n| caption = Campuses in Austin\n}}\n\nHyde Park High School is a ministry of Hyde Park Baptist Church in Austin, Texas. The High School is located at 11400 N. Mopac, Austin, Texas. Enrollment generally runs from 200-300 students. It moved to this location in the fall of 2009. Before this time it was located at 3901 Speedway with the Elementary and Middle School campuses. It was founded in 1980 by Bob Edd Shotwell, who also founded Hyde Park Baptist Elementary in 1968.\n\n== Associations ==\n\nThe school is now a member of the [[Association of Christian Schools International]] (ACSI), the [[Southern Baptist]] Association of Christian Schools (SBACS), and Texas Association of Private and Parochial Schools (TAPPS).{{Citation needed|date=September 2009|reason=Those should probably be sourced or dropped.}}\n\n== Extracurricular activities ==\n===Sports===\nHyde Park athletics is led by [[athletic director]]/head [[American football|football]] coach Dean Campbell. Dean Campbell has coached at the college football level at many different universities, including the University of Texas, Texas A&M University, Texas Tech, Arkansas, and Air Force. Campbell's goal for Hyde Park athletics is stated as \"One foundational goal for our program is to provide strong leadership for our student athletes through the Christian role models of our coaches.\"\n* [[American football|Football]]\n* [[Volleyball]]\n* [[Basketball]] (Boys and Girls)\n* [[Cross Country Running|Cross Country]]\n* [[Track and field|Track]]\n* [[Association football|Soccer]] (Boys and Girls)\n* [[Golf]]\n* [[Baseball]]\n* [[Softball]]\n* [[Tennis]] (Boys and Girls)\n* [[Cheerleading]]\n* [[